  "text": "Our study has several limitations. First, our meta-analysis is based on a small number of studies exclusively from Eastern Asia. Thus, our findings may not be generalizable to the populations in other regions. Second, our descriptive assessment of model performance is exploratory, based on the available cumulative count data with inconsistent follow-up periods and heterogeneous methods adopted to verify gastric cancer cases. Assessing how these affect the model performance would need data at the level of the individual. Third, the small number of eligible studies precluded subgroup analyses or meta-regression for H. pylori antibody assays. Therefore, how each different assay affects the results is unclear. Fourth, H. pylori and gastric atrophy are generally believed to be more relevant in the pathogenesis of intestinal type gastric cancer [CITATION_1] . Few studies with the pertinent information precluded the subgroup analyses by histological subtype. Lastly, publication bias is still of concern because our searches were limited to the English-and Japanese-language literature.",
